<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title><%- title %></title>
    <meta name="author" content="Ulises Cabrera">
		<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-1q8mTJOASx8j1Au+a5WDVnPi2lkFfwwEAa8hDDdjZlpLegxhjVME1fgjWPGmkzs7" crossorigin="anonymous">
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-12">
          <div class="jumbotron">
            <h1><%= title %></h1>
            <p>A microservice where the user can pass a URL as a parameter and it will receive a shortened URL in the JSON response, 
             If it pass an invalid URL that doesn't follow the valid http://www.example.com format, the JSON response will contain an error instead.
             And when the user visits that shortened URL, it will redirect it to the original link.</p>
          </div>   
          
            <h3>Example creation usage:</h3>
            <div class="well well-sm">
              <p class="text-danger">
              <%= baseUrl %>new/https://www.google.com<br>
              <%= baseUrl %>new/http://nba.com
              </p>
            </div>
            <h3>Example creation output:</h3>
            <div class="well well-sm">
              <p class="text-danger">
            { "original_url": "http://nba.com", "short_url": "<%= baseUrl %>6" }
              </p>
            </div>
            <h3>Usage:</h3>
            <div class="well well-sm">
              <p class="text-danger">
                <%= baseUrl %>6
              </p>
            </div>
            <h3>Will Redirect To:</h3>
            <div class="well well-sm">
              <p class="text-danger">
                http://nba.com
              </p>
            </div>              
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </body>
</html>